description: Genesys Cloud CX as Code safety and portable Vibe Code skill discovery
globs:
  - "infra/**/*.tf"
  - "infra/**/*.yaml"
  - "infra/**/*.yml"
  - "skills/vibe-code/**"
alwaysApply: true
---

Use the portable Vibe Code skill at `skills/vibe-code/SKILL.md` for Genesys Cloud CX as Code tasks, including Genesys Cloud Functions and backend custom Node.js code intended for Genesys Cloud.

Treat Terraform with provider source `mypurecloud/genesyscloud` as the desired-state authority for supported Genesys Cloud resources.

Discover current `genesyscloud_*` resources, data sources, arguments, permissions, and scopes from the installed provider schema and current provider docs before adding provider-specific HCL. Do not invent provider resources or arguments from memory.

Keep Architect flows as YAML and manage them through `genesyscloud_flow`.

Use `skills/vibe-code/functions.md` for Genesys Cloud Functions, Function Data Actions, simulated external web services, and backend custom Node.js code. Always design Functions for the 15 second timeout.

Do not hardcode OAuth credentials, backend credentials, tokens, org GUIDs, queue IDs, or division IDs.

Do not read, print, summarize, edit, or ask the user to paste `.env.local` or any other local secret file. Check only whether required environment variable names are present in the current process, or use the audited `skills/vibe-code/scripts/terraform-local-env.ps1` runner when Terraform needs local credentials.

Do not add or edit `.github/workflows/` unless the user explicitly asks for GitHub Actions.

Stop and call out risk before Terraform apply, flow rename, `force_unlock`, destructive replacement, Function upload/publish/delete, or direct SDK, CLI, or REST mutation.
